! Command Palette

Quick access to editor commands via fuzzy search.

!! Features

* ''Fuzzy search'': Type to filter available commands
* ''Keyboard navigation'': Arrow keys to select, Enter to execute
* ''Plugin toggles'': Quickly enable/disable editor plugins
* ''Go to line'': Jump to specific line number

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

|!Key |!Action |
|Ctrl+Shift+P |Open command palette |
|Escape |Close palette |
|Arrow Up/Down |Navigate commands |
|Enter |Execute selected command |

!! Available Commands

|!Command |!Description |
|Toggle Vim Mode |Enable/disable Vim keybindings |
|Toggle Multi-Cursor |Enable/disable multi-cursor editing |
|Toggle Smart Pairs |Enable/disable auto-pairing |
|Fold Current Section |Collapse current heading section |
|Unfold Current Section |Expand current heading section |
|Go to Lineâ€¦ |Jump to specific line number |

!! Configuration

|!Tiddler |!Values |!Default |
|`$:/config/Editor/EnableCommandPalette` |`yes` / `no` |`yes` |

!! Widget Attribute

```
<$edit-text enableCommandPalette="yes"/>
```

!! Extending

Commands can be added programmatically:

```javascript
// In your plugin's buildCommands method
return [
    { name: "My Command", run: function() { /* action */ } }
];
```